{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9d1bccaa-7826-48cd-8636-40586b1d47b4","content":"No files found in the workspace. Since there's no existing project, I'll explain the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings. Here's the pattern:\n\n```xml\n<!-- SettingsPage.xaml -->\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Add `xmlns:vm`** — import the namespace containing your ViewModel.\n2. **Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** on the `ContentPage` — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the `BindingContext`, enabling compile-time checking of all `{Binding ...}` expressions.\n\n### Catching binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated **during compilation** — if you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Fonsize}`), you get a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo ensure this works:\n\n| Setting | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| **Enable XamlC** | On by default in .NET MAUI. Verify no `[assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Skip)]` exists. |\n| **Treat warnings as errors** *(optional)* | Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to fail the build on binding-related warnings. |\n| **Opt out locally** | If a binding must be dynamic (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate` with a different type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings for that subtree. |\n\nThat's all — the `x:DataType` attribute is the single change that converts regular bindings into compiled bindings.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ae316acf-5d71-4b1e-9d03-dde54bad5d40","outputTokens":708,"requestId":"A433:32D1ED:611426D:697AE9D:69F00424"},"id":"5fb62698-17e5-4434-b3d2-758efa988b32","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:55.466Z","parentId":"bbcb0bf6-6723-45c4-ba62-114e3f9d1043"}
